const CHARACTERS = [
  { id:"cloud", name:"Cloud Strife", faction:"avalanche", role:"Ex-SOLDIER (claimed) · Mercenary",
    personality:"Outwardly cold, terse and standoffish, he wears a mercenary's 'not interested' bravado to keep everyone at arm's length. Beneath it is a deeply insecure young man desperate to matter, prone to dissociation and self-doubt. As he heals, a dry-humored, fiercely protective and quietly gentle leader emerges.",
    bio:"A spiky-haired swordsman hired by AVALANCHE, carrying the enormous Buster Sword. He insists he was a member of SOLDIER 1st Class.",
    spoilerBio:"Cloud never made SOLDIER. After Nibelheim he was a failed Jenova-cell experiment of Hojo's; his confident 'ex-SOLDIER' persona is stitched together from Zack's memories and Tifa's stories. Tifa helps him rebuild his true self in the Lifestream.",
    background:[
      "Cloud grew up in Nibelheim a lonely, bullied boy with no father and few friends. He idolized the village's beauty, Tifa Lockhart, from a distance, and the night before he left for the city he met her at the old well and made a promise: he would join SOLDIER, become a hero like the great Sephiroth, and come back to save her if she were ever in trouble. That promise — to be someone worth admiring — is the seed of everything that breaks in him.",
      "He failed. Cloud never had the strength of will to pass into SOLDIER and became an ordinary, anonymous Shinra infantryman. He was so ashamed that when his unit returned to Nibelheim five years later, he kept his helmet on the entire time so no one — least of all Tifa — would recognize the boy who didn't make it.",
      "Then Nibelheim burned. After Sephiroth's massacre, Hojo seized the surviving Cloud and Zack as Jenova-cell specimens and kept them in Mako tanks for roughly four years. The prolonged Mako exposure dissolved Cloud's already-fragile sense of self into near-catatonia. When the two finally escaped and Zack — the real SOLDIER 1st, the genuine hero — was gunned down shielding him, the broken, Jenova-influenced Cloud filled the void where his identity used to be by absorbing Zack's: his rank, his sword, his mannerisms, his memories.",
      "So the confident 'ex-SOLDIER Cloud' the party first meets is a construct — a patchwork of who he wished he was, the stories Tifa told, and the life Zack actually lived. His swagger is borrowed; his memories are partly someone else's. Tifa senses the wrongness but, fearing what the truth might do to him (and to her own guilt), says nothing.",
      "Sephiroth turns this fault line into a weapon — and the Black Materia is how he proves it. At the Temple of the Ancients the party discovers the Temple itself IS the Black Materia, the spell that calls down Meteor, and that claiming it means shrinking the whole structure into a single orb. Because Cloud is saturated with Jenova's cells, Sephiroth can reach into his mind like a puppeteer: he compels Cloud to retrieve the Black Materia and place it personally into Sephiroth's hand, even forcing him to beat down his own friends to do it. Cloud carries and surrenders the most dangerous object on the Planet not by choice but as living proof of Sephiroth's claim that he has no will of his own.",
      "Sephiroth drives the point home: Cloud is no one — a manufactured Jenova clone with implanted memories, a doll that does as it's told — and the accusation lands because part of it is true. Cloud's mind collapses, and afterward he falls into the Lifestream a hollow shell of Mako poisoning.",
      "His salvation is Tifa, the one person who shared the real Nibelheim. Inside his own subconscious, drifting in the Lifestream, she walks him back through his true memories and helps him see that he doesn't have to be the invented hero to be real. The Cloud who emerges is not the SOLDIER fantasy — he's an ordinary, flawed young man who was there, who cared, and who is, in the end, enough. Only as himself can he finally stand against Sephiroth — and the long shadow of that identity wound still flickers through Advent Children, where guilt and fear of loss nearly pull him under again."
    ],
    bgSpoiler:true,
    tidbit:"At the Gold Saucer, a hidden 'affection' system tracks your dialogue choices and decides who joins Cloud on the gondola date. Most players get Aerith or Tifa — but with the right (wrong?) choices, you can end up on a romantic date with Barret.",
    portrait:{ skin:"#ecc6a0", hair:"#f2d65c", style:"spiky", eyes:"#5fe3ff", glow:true, clothes:"#22323e" } },

  { id:"tifa", name:"Tifa Lockhart", faction:"avalanche", role:"Martial artist · Barkeep of Seventh Heaven",
    personality:"Warm, nurturing and dependable — the emotional anchor who holds the group together. She buries her own grief to care for others, sometimes to a fault, and shrinks from hard conversations. Under the gentleness is real steel: a fighter who never backs down when those she loves are threatened.",
    bio:"Cloud's childhood friend from Nibelheim and a core member of AVALANCHE. She fights with her fists and runs the bar that hides the group's operations.",
    background:[
      "Tifa was the cherished daughter of one of Nibelheim's leading families, and a quietly determined girl. When her mother died, she set off up Mt. Nibel believing she could reach her — a fall on that climb badly injured her and left Cloud, who'd followed her, blamed by the village. It deepened the bond between them even as it pushed them apart.",
      "She survived the night Sephiroth burned Nibelheim only because the travelling martial-arts master Zangan pulled her from the flames and carried her to safety. Trained by him, she grew into a formidable monk-style fighter and eventually opened Seventh Heaven in the Sector 7 slums — a bar that doubled as the secret hideout of Barret's AVALANCHE.",
      "When a hollow-eyed Cloud reappeared years later, Tifa recognized that his memories were subtly, frighteningly wrong, but she kept quiet — partly to protect him, partly from her own guilt and fear. It is ultimately Tifa who descends into the Lifestream with him and reassembles the real Cloud, making her not just the heart of the party but the key to its hero."
    ],
    bgSpoiler:true,
    tidbit:"Tifa was a late addition to the cast, created largely to form a love triangle with Aerith. An early design document infamously described a version of the plot where Aerith's death pushes Tifa and Cloud together — fueling decades of 'who does Cloud love?' debate.",
    portrait:{ skin:"#f0caa6", hair:"#2e2422", style:"long", eyes:"#7a3a48", clothes:"#2a2f36" } },

  { id:"aerith", name:"Aerith Gainsborough", faction:"cetra", role:"Flower girl · Last of the Cetra",
    personality:"Bright, playful and disarmingly forward, with a mischievous, flirtatious confidence that hides how much she carries. Selfless and serene about her own fate, she meets a doomed world with humor and grace rather than despair.",
    bio:"A kind flower-seller from the Midgar slums, pursued by Shinra for her heritage. She can hear the voice of the Planet.",
    spoilerBio:"The last living Cetra. At the Forgotten Capital she prays to summon Holy — the only thing that can stop Meteor — and is struck down by Sephiroth mid-prayer. Her spirit guides the Lifestream to answer that prayer.",
    background:[
      "Aerith is the daughter of Professor Gast, the Shinra scientist who founded the Jenova Project, and Ifalna, one of the very last true Cetra. After Gast realized Jenova was the Calamity rather than an Ancient and fled Shinra, Hojo hunted him down, murdered him, and dragged Ifalna and the infant Aerith back to the labs as specimens.",
      "Ifalna eventually escaped with seven-year-old Aerith but died on the platform of the Midgar train station. A kind widow, Elmyra, took the orphaned girl in and raised her in the Sector 5 slums, where Aerith grew flowers in the only patch of earth in Midgar that would still let anything bloom.",
      "All her life she could faintly hear the voice of the Planet, and all her life the Turks watched her — Shinra coveting the last Cetra as a key to the fabled Promised Land. She fell for a cheerful SOLDIER named Zack, who vanished and never returned, before crossing paths with a strikingly similar mercenary named Cloud.",
      "Knowing, perhaps, where her path led, Aerith slipped away to the Forgotten Capital to pray for Holy — the only force that could answer Sephiroth's Meteor. Sephiroth killed her as the prayer completed. But her spirit did not leave: from within the Lifestream she guided Holy and the Planet's own energy to repel Meteor, and her blessing later washes the Geostigma from the world in Advent Children. Death made her, if anything, more present in the story than before."
    ],
    bgSpoiler:true,
    tidbit:"In the 1997 English release she was named 'Aeris' — the intended romanization is 'Aerith,' a play on 'Earth.' Her death also birthed gaming's most enduring hoax: elaborate fake instructions for 'reviving Aerith' circulated for years, none of them real.",
    portrait:{ skin:"#f2cda8", hair:"#6e4a2f", style:"braid", eyes:"#54b85f", clothes:"#b6324a", acc:["bow"] } },

  { id:"barret", name:"Barret Wallace", faction:"avalanche", role:"Leader of AVALANCHE",
    personality:"Loud, brash and quick to anger, swearing up a storm and charging in fists-first. The bluster masks a tender, guilt-ridden father and idealist who agonizes over the lives his cause costs. Loyal to a fault, and endlessly devoted to his daughter.",
    bio:"The hot-blooded leader of an AVALANCHE cell, with a gun grafted to his right arm. He wages war on Shinra to save the Planet — and to avenge his hometown of Corel.",
    background:[
      "Barret was born in the coal-mining town of Corel. When Shinra proposed converting the town to a Mako reactor, Barret championed the deal, believing it would bring prosperity — a choice he never forgives himself for. After a reactor incident, Shinra torched Corel to cover it up, killing Barret's wife Myrna and maiming both Barret and his best friend Dyne, who each lost a hand in the disaster.",
      "Barret replaced his with a gun. He took in Dyne's orphaned daughter Marlene and raised her as his own, channeling his grief and guilt into AVALANCHE — a cell of eco-warriors striking at Shinra's reactors to stop the draining of the Planet. The bombings' civilian cost weighs on him constantly, and much of his arc is learning that righteous rage and responsibility aren't the same thing.",
      "Reuniting with the broken, murderous Dyne at the Gold Saucer forces Barret to confront the man he could have become — and to carry Marlene's true parentage as a quiet promise."
    ],
    bgSpoiler:true,
    tidbit:"Barret's design — the build, the attitude, the arm-cannon — is widely read as an homage to Mr. T, and his story beats lift from action cinema of the era. He's also the franchise's first prominently featured Black playable character.",
    portrait:{ skin:"#6e4a35", hair:"#16140f", style:"buzz", eyes:"#241c14", clothes:"#3c5a3a", acc:["beard","shades"] } },

  { id:"redxiii", name:"Red XIII", short:"Red", keys:["Nanaki","Red XIII"], faction:"ally", role:"Beast of Cosmo Canyon",
    personality:"Speaks with the calm, measured wisdom of a scholar far older than he looks — yet a proud adolescent's insecurity flares when his courage is questioned. Noble, loyal and curious, he matures from a self-conscious youth into a true guardian of his people.",
    bio:"A fanged, fire-tailed creature freed from Hojo's lab. Far more intelligent and noble than he appears, he is the grandson of Bugenhagen and a guardian of Cosmo Canyon.",
    tidbit:"'Red XIII' is just Hojo's experiment label — his real name is Nanaki. Though he sounds like a wise elder, he's only around 48 in a species that lives for centuries, making him roughly a teenager. By the time of Advent Children he has cubs of his own.",
    portrait:{ skin:"#d7572a", hair:"#b33d1e", style:"beast", eyes:"#f0c040", clothes:"#8a2e15", acc:["scar"] } },

  { id:"cid", name:"Cid Highwind", faction:"ally", role:"Pilot · Would-be astronaut",
    personality:"Foul-mouthed, gruff and perpetually chain-smoking, Cid hides bitter disappointment behind constant cursing and a short fuse. Beneath the rough exterior is a brilliant, big-dreaming engineer with a stubborn, never-say-die spirit — and a surprising tenderness.",
    bio:"A veteran pilot whose dream of spaceflight was crushed by Shinra's collapsing space program. He flies the airship Highwind for the party.",
    tidbit:"Nearly every Final Fantasy has a 'Cid,' but FFVII's is the only one who becomes a fully playable party member and, by the ending cutscene, effectively the one narrating humanity's place on the Planet. His dream rocket, Shinra No. 26, finally flies in the side-quest to the space program.",
    portrait:{ skin:"#e3bd92", hair:"#c9b079", style:"messy", eyes:"#3a6ea5", clothes:"#2b3a44", acc:["goggles"] } },

  { id:"yuffie", name:"Yuffie Kisaragi", faction:"ally", role:"Wutai ninja · Materia hunter",
    personality:"Hyperactive, boastful and shamelessly greedy for Materia, Yuffie is comic relief with a mischievous grin and zero impulse control. But the antics cover genuine patriotism and a teenager's wounded pride over her conquered homeland — and real courage when it counts.",
    bio:"A young ninja from Wutai who joins the party largely to steal their Materia. Beneath the mischief is fierce loyalty to her defeated home.",
    tidbit:"Yuffie is entirely optional — you only recruit her by winning a random battle in a forest and surviving her dialogue traps. Miss her, and you'll later miss her Wutai sidequest, where she can steal ALL of your Materia and force a frantic chase to get it back.",
    portrait:{ skin:"#f0caa6", hair:"#26242a", style:"short", eyes:"#3a2e2e", clothes:"#2f6f54", acc:["headband"] } },

  { id:"vincent", name:"Vincent Valentine", faction:"turks", role:"Former Turk · Host of Chaos",
    personality:"Brooding, taciturn and haunted, Vincent speaks rarely and broods often, convinced he deserves his suffering as penance. Coldly composed in battle, he is at heart a romantic crushed by guilt — loyal, principled, and quietly desperate for redemption.",
    bio:"A gunman found sleeping in a coffin beneath the Shinra Manor, wracked by guilt over his past as a Turk.",
    spoilerBio:"Hojo shot Vincent and used his body for experiments, leaving him near-immortal and able to transform into demons — including Chaos. In Dirge of Cerberus he wields the Protomateria against Deepground's Omega. He loved Lucrecia, Sephiroth's mother.",
    background:[
      "Vincent was a Turk assigned to guard the scientists of the Jenova Project, where he fell in love with the researcher Lucrecia Crescent. When she agreed to carry Hojo's experimental child — the infant who would become Sephiroth — Vincent's failure to stop her became the central guilt of his life.",
      "Hojo shot Vincent and turned his body into an experiment, grafting demonic transformations onto him and leaving him functionally immortal. Unable to die and unwilling to live, Vincent sealed himself in a coffin beneath the Shinra Manor to sleep off a penance with no end, until the party wakes him.",
      "Decades later, in Dirge of Cerberus, his buried history resurfaces: the Protomateria within him is the key to controlling the demon Chaos, and the child-warrior Shelke carries Lucrecia's preserved memories. Confronting Deepground, Omega, and the truth about Lucrecia, Vincent finally begins to forgive himself."
    ],
    bgSpoiler:true,
    tidbit:"Vincent is completely missable: he stays asleep unless you crack the safe in the Shinra Manor (combination Right 36, Left 10, Right 59, Right 97), beat the boss inside, and choose to wake him. Fan demand for this optional character is what earned him his own game, Dirge of Cerberus.",
    portrait:{ skin:"#ead2c2", hair:"#14110f", style:"veiled", eyes:"#e23a3a", glow:true, clothes:"#6a1414", acc:["headband"] } },

  { id:"reeve", name:"Reeve Tuesti", short:"Reeve", keys:["Reeve","Cait Sith"], faction:"shinra", role:"Shinra exec · Operator of Cait Sith",
    personality:"Conscientious, soft-spoken and torn — a company man whose decency keeps overriding his orders. Through the cheeky, fortune-telling bravado of his Cait Sith puppet, his real warmth and guilt slip through. Ultimately an idealist who chooses the Planet over the paycheck.",
    bio:"Head of Shinra's Urban Development. He remote-controls Cait Sith, the fortune-telling robot cat that travels with the party.",
    spoilerBio:"Cait Sith is Reeve's puppet — at first a Shinra spy planted in the group. His conscience wins out; he defects and later founds the World Regenesis Organization to heal the Planet after Meteorfall.",
    tidbit:"Cait Sith is the only 'character' who dies and is simply replaced — when the first unit sacrifices itself, Reeve calmly sends in a second Cait Sith. Because Reeve operates the doll remotely, he's also the one party 'member' who is never actually physically present.",
    portrait:{ skin:"#e3bd92", hair:"#2a2622", style:"neat", eyes:"#4a3a2e", clothes:"#2a2f3a", acc:["beard"] } },

  { id:"sephiroth", name:"Sephiroth", faction:"antagonist", role:"Legendary SOLDIER 1st Class",
    personality:"Once a composed, almost gentle prodigy, Sephiroth becomes the embodiment of cold, godlike megalomania. Serene, eloquent and utterly without mercy, he treats all life as beneath him. His calm, knowing menace and absolute conviction make him as seductive as he is terrifying.",
    bio:"The most celebrated war hero Shinra ever produced — a silver-haired swordsman wielding the impossibly long Masamune, idolized across the world.",
    spoilerBio:"Discovering he was a Jenova-cell experiment, Sephiroth went mad and burned Nibelheim. Believing Jenova to be his mother and the Cetra his birthright, he seeks to wound the Planet with Meteor, ride its healing Lifestream, and ascend to godhood. The biological son of Hojo and Lucrecia.",
    background:[
      "Sephiroth was the masterwork of the Jenova Project: the unborn child of the scientists Hojo and Lucrecia Crescent, injected with the cells of the creature Shinra believed to be an Ancient. He was raised as a specimen and a weapon, never knowing his mother, told almost nothing of his origin.",
      "He grew into the single greatest SOLDIER who ever lived — the hero of the Wutai War, the face on every recruitment poster, a swordsman of impossible grace with the long Masamune. For a time he was, by the accounts of those who knew him, composed and even kind. The cracks showed only as his fellow 1st Classes, Genesis and Angeal, began to 'degrade,' raising questions about what they — and he — really were.",
      "The break came in the basement library of the Shinra Manor in Nibelheim. Reading Gast's and Hojo's research, Sephiroth concluded he was the last son of the Cetra, that 'Jenova' was his mother, and that the Ancients' planet had been stolen from his kind by ordinary humans. He burned Nibelheim to the ground and descended into the reactor to claim Jenova — until a nameless infantryman ran him through.",
      "But Sephiroth did not simply die. His will, carried by Jenova's cells spread through the Lifestream and through every specimen Hojo ever made, persists like a virus. His grand design: drive Meteor into the Planet to inflict a catastrophic wound, gather the Lifestream's healing energy as it rushes to the injury, and absorb that god-power to become one with the Planet itself.",
      "Defeated at Meteorfall, his will simply waits. In Advent Children his Remnants — Kadaj, Loz, Yazoo — gather the last of 'Mother' so he can be reborn; he returns again in the Remake saga, now seemingly aware of the timeline's fate, taunting Cloud with knowledge of things that haven't happened yet. He is less a man than an idea that refuses to stop returning."
    ],
    bgSpoiler:true,
    tidbit:"His boss theme 'One-Winged Angel' sets choral Latin lifted from Carl Orff's Carmina Burana ('Estuans interius...'). Composer Nobuo Uematsu deliberately built it from short looping fragments, inspired by Stravinsky and Jimi Hendrix — the first orchestral-choral track in a Final Fantasy.",
    portrait:{ skin:"#ecd8cc", hair:"#dadfe2", style:"long", eyes:"#43d977", glow:true, slit:true, clothes:"#14161a", acc:["wing"] } },

  { id:"zack", name:"Zack Fair", faction:"soldier", role:"SOLDIER 1st Class",
    personality:"Earnest, exuberant and relentlessly optimistic, Zack treats everyone as a friend. Loyal, dutiful and a little goofy, he lives by 'dreams and honor' and gives everything — even his life — for the people he loves.",
    bio:"A big-hearted SOLDIER who befriends Cloud and falls for Aerith. Wielder of the Buster Sword and hero of Crisis Core.",
    spoilerBio:"Branded a traitor after Nibelheim, Zack escapes Hojo's lab dragging the comatose Cloud to safety. Gunned down by Shinra troops outside Midgar, he passes his sword and his 'living legacy' to Cloud — whose very identity is shaped by him.",
    background:[
      "Zack was a country boy from Gongaga who rose to SOLDIER 1st Class under the mentorship of Angeal Hewley, inheriting both Angeal's Buster Sword and his creed: protect your honor and your dreams. Energetic and irrepressibly friendly, he befriended a shy infantryman named Cloud and fell in love with a flower girl named Aerith in the Sector 5 slums.",
      "After Nibelheim, Zack and Cloud were taken by Hojo as Jenova-cell specimens. Zack broke them both out and carried the Mako-poisoned, near-comatose Cloud across the wilderness toward Midgar, dreaming of becoming a mercenary and living a normal life.",
      "Just outside the city, the Shinra army caught them. Zack fought off wave after wave alone and fell to a final volley of gunfire. With his last strength he passed the Buster Sword to Cloud and told him to live on as his 'living legacy' — words that would echo, half-remembered, through Cloud's stolen sense of self for the rest of the saga."
    ],
    bgSpoiler:true,
    tidbit:"In the original 1997 game Zack appears only in brief, blurry flashbacks and is never even named on screen for most players. His popularity from those fragments is what led Square to build an entire prequel, Crisis Core, around him a decade later.",
    portrait:{ skin:"#e8c39a", hair:"#1a1a20", style:"spiky", eyes:"#43c8e6", glow:true, clothes:"#2a2f36", acc:["scar"] } },

  { id:"jenova", name:"Jenova", faction:"antagonist", role:"The Calamity from the Skies",
    personality:"Not a personality so much as a hunger — a parasitic intelligence that mimics, infects and consumes. It has no voice of its own, only the borrowed faces and will it wears, spreading itself through every host it touches.",
    bio:"A mysterious specimen unearthed in a 2000-year-old rock stratum, revered by Shinra's science department as an 'Ancient'.",
    spoilerBio:"Not a Cetra at all, but a parasitic alien lifeform that crashed into the Planet long ago, nearly exterminating the Cetra by infection and mimicry. Its cells, threaded through Sephiroth and countless experiments, let his will spread like a virus.",
    tidbit:"Every Jenova boss is named with a suffix — Jenova∙BIRTH, ∙LIFE, ∙DEATH, ∙SYNTHESIS — marking the creature being reassembled across the game. Despite being called Sephiroth's 'mother,' Jenova has no gender and isn't his parent at all; the maternal bond exists only in his deluded mind.",
    portrait:{ skin:"#c79be0", hair:"#8a5fb0", style:"alien", eyes:"#e85bff", glow:true, clothes:"#3a2150" } },

  { id:"president", name:"President Shinra", short:"President", keys:["President Shinra"], faction:"shinra", role:"President of Shinra Inc.",
    personality:"A smug, complacent tycoon who measures the world in profit and sees the Planet as a resource to be strip-mined. Arrogant and short-sighted, he rules through bribery and force, never imagining his empire could outgrow his grip.",
    bio:"The ruthless head of the corporation that rules the world through Mako energy. He treats the Planet's lifeblood as a quarterly figure.",
    spoilerBio:"Found impaled in his office, the Masamune through his back — the first sign that Sephiroth still walks. His son Rufus seizes control in the chaos.",
    tidbit:"He's the first major boss-tier obstacle of the game, yet you never actually fight him — he's assassinated off-handedly by Sephiroth the moment you escape Shinra HQ, a deliberate beat that announces the real villain has arrived.",
    portrait:{ skin:"#e8c39a", hair:"#cfcabc", style:"bald", eyes:"#4a3a2e", clothes:"#3a3326", acc:["mustache"] } },

  { id:"rufus", name:"Rufus Shinra", faction:"shinra", role:"Vice-President → President",
    personality:"Cold, calculating and quietly ruthless, Rufus is everything his father was not: disciplined, modern and unsentimental. He believes the world is best ruled through fear — yet after Meteorfall a flicker of conscience drives him to atone for Shinra's sins.",
    bio:"The cold heir to Shinra who takes the company by the reins after the President's death, intent on ruling through power rather than bribery.",
    tidbit:"Everyone assumed Rufus died when Diamond WEAPON blasted Shinra HQ — including the developers, narratively. He turns up alive in Advent Children, cloaked and wheelchair-bound with Geostigma, having quietly kept Jenova's head hidden the whole time.",
    portrait:{ skin:"#ecc6a0", hair:"#ecdf9a", style:"neat", eyes:"#6a86a8", clothes:"#e8e4d8" } },

  { id:"hojo", name:"Hojo", keys:["Hojo"], faction:"shinra", role:"Professor · Head of the Science Department",
    personality:"Gleefully amoral and consumed by scientific obsession, Hojo views every living thing — including his own son — as an experiment. Petty, smug and utterly without empathy, he is the banal, grinning face of evil in a lab coat.",
    bio:"Shinra's chief scientist, obsessed with Jenova, the Cetra and the limits of life. He sees people only as specimens.",
    spoilerBio:"Architect of the Jenova Project. He fathered Sephiroth with Lucrecia and injected the unborn child with Jenova cells; he experimented on Vincent, Cloud, Zack and Red XIII, and murdered his rival Gast. In the end he tries to fuse with Jenova himself.",
    tidbit:"Hojo's casual cruelty has a grimly funny edge: the optional Lucrecia backstory reveals he genuinely doesn't seem to care that Sephiroth is his own son. In the ending he injects himself with Jenova cells purely out of scientific curiosity, becoming the final-dungeon boss 'Helletic/Lifeform Hojo.'",
    portrait:{ skin:"#d8c2a8", hair:"#2a2622", style:"neat", eyes:"#3a3a3a", clothes:"#cfd2d4", acc:["glasses","ponytail"] } },

  { id:"reno", name:"Reno", faction:"turks", role:"Turk",
    personality:"Laid-back, wisecracking and allergic to hard work, Reno does Shinra's dirty jobs with a shrug and a smirk. Beneath the slacker charm is a lethal professional with an oddly principled streak and genuine loyalty to his partner.",
    bio:"A red-haired Turk who fights with an electro-mag rod — easygoing, reluctant about the dirty work, but devastatingly effective.",
    tidbit:"Reno is the Turk who actually presses the button to drop the Sector 7 plate — and the games never quite let him off the hook for it, even as he becomes a fan-favorite comic-relief antagonist who'll happily team up with Cloud when the Planet itself is on the line.",
    portrait:{ skin:"#ecc6a0", hair:"#c2402c", style:"slick", eyes:"#54b85f", clothes:"#14161a", acc:["ponytail","goggles"] } },

  { id:"rude", name:"Rude", faction:"turks", role:"Turk",
    personality:"A stoic man of almost no words, Rude lets his fists and dark glasses do the talking. Intensely professional and unshakably loyal, he hides a soft, sentimental heart — and a not-so-secret crush — behind the silence.",
    bio:"Reno's bald, sunglasses-wearing partner: a man of very few words and devastating fists.",
    tidbit:"Rude's not-so-secret crush is on Tifa — a running gag the games lean into, including moments where he conspicuously 'hesitates' to fight her. He owns an apparently identical collection of sunglasses and is rarely, if ever, seen without a pair.",
    portrait:{ skin:"#6e4a35", hair:"#0e0e0e", style:"bald", eyes:"#241c14", clothes:"#14161a", acc:["shades"] } },

  { id:"tseng", name:"Tseng", faction:"turks", role:"Leader of the Turks",
    personality:"Composed, disciplined and quietly authoritative, Tseng carries the weight of command with cool professionalism. Loyal to Shinra yet privately conflicted, he harbors a tender, unspoken concern for Aerith that he never lets compromise his duty.",
    bio:"The composed commander of the Turks, answering directly to Shinra's top brass — with a long-standing, careful watch over Aerith.",
    tidbit:"Tseng has shadowed Aerith since she was a child; in the Turks' prequel Before Crisis it's clear his feelings run deeper than duty. He's nearly killed at the Temple of the Ancients, and his survival was left ambiguous for years before later entries confirmed it.",
    portrait:{ skin:"#e8c8a0", hair:"#16120f", style:"neat", eyes:"#241c14", clothes:"#14161a", acc:["ponytail"] } },

  { id:"elena", name:"Elena", faction:"turks", role:"Turk (rookie)",
    personality:"Earnest, hot-headed and eager to prove herself, the rookie Turk wears her heart on her sleeve. Prone to nerves and outbursts, she is fiercely devoted to her team — and not shy about her feelings for Tseng.",
    bio:"The newest of the Turks, determined to prove herself and intensely loyal to Tseng and the team.",
    tidbit:"Elena is the only Turk in the original game's core trio with no Before Crisis backstory — she's the rookie precisely because she joined last. Her older sister Emma is a veteran Turk in supplementary material, making the Turks something of a family business.",
    portrait:{ skin:"#f0caa6", hair:"#e6cf86", style:"short", eyes:"#6a5a3a", clothes:"#14161a" } },

  { id:"cissnei", name:"Cissnei", faction:"turks", role:"Turk",
    personality:"Kind, level-headed and warmer than a Turk has any right to be, Cissnei is torn between duty and decency. Her quiet loyalty to Zack repeatedly leads her to bend the rules, revealing a conscience the job tries to erase.",
    bio:"A young Turk who wields a giant shuriken and befriends Zack, repeatedly risking herself to help him.",
    tidbit:"'Cissnei' is a codename — her giant cross-shaped shuriken, 'Rekka,' and her gentle handling of Zack made her one of Crisis Core's most beloved additions. Developers have hinted she may be connected to the Turk who appears in the optional Wutai material, though it's never confirmed.",
    portrait:{ skin:"#f0caa6", hair:"#b06a4a", style:"short", eyes:"#6a4a3a", clothes:"#14161a" } },

  { id:"genesis", name:"Genesis Rhapsodos", faction:"soldier", role:"SOLDIER 1st Class",
    personality:"Theatrical, vain and consumed by his own legend, Genesis quotes the poem LOVELESS at every turn and craves recognition above all. Brilliant and proud, his envy and existential terror at his own decay curdle into obsession and ruin.",
    bio:"A flamboyant SOLDIER once equal to Sephiroth in fame, forever reciting the epic poem LOVELESS.",
    spoilerBio:"A product of Project G, Genesis began to 'degrade' and deserted Shinra, mass-producing copies of himself and dragging Angeal down with him — the spark that set the whole tragedy in motion.",
    tidbit:"Genesis was modeled on and voiced (in Japanese) by Gackt, the Japanese rock star, who also wrote songs for Crisis Core. The poem he endlessly quotes, LOVELESS, was written specifically for the game and is treated in-world as Shinra's national epic.",
    portrait:{ skin:"#ecc6a0", hair:"#a83a2a", style:"neat", eyes:"#43c8e6", glow:true, clothes:"#6a1414" } },

  { id:"angeal", name:"Angeal Hewley", faction:"soldier", role:"SOLDIER 1st Class",
    personality:"Stern, principled and endlessly devoted to 'honor and dreams', Angeal is the moral compass who mentors Zack like a younger brother. Dignified and self-sacrificing, he would rather die than betray his ideals or become a monster.",
    bio:"Zack's honor-bound mentor and the original owner of the Buster Sword, which he keeps pristine as a symbol of his pride.",
    spoilerBio:"Like Genesis, an experimental being who begins to degrade and mutate. Unable to bear what he is becoming, he forces Zack to end his life — passing on the Buster Sword and the creed Zack will later give Cloud.",
    tidbit:"Angeal's degraded form sprouts a single white wing — the visual rhyme with Sephiroth's single black wing is deliberate, marking them as kindred 'monsters.' The Buster Sword passes Angeal → Zack → Cloud, making it the literal heirloom that links all three swordsmen.",
    portrait:{ skin:"#e3bd92", hair:"#1a1a20", style:"neat", eyes:"#43c8e6", glow:true, clothes:"#2a2f36" } },

  { id:"lucrecia", name:"Lucrecia Crescent", faction:"shinra", role:"Shinra scientist",
    personality:"Gentle, brilliant and tragically self-punishing, Lucrecia is a scientist whose ambition and guilt destroy her. Torn between love and duty, she makes one catastrophic choice and spends eternity unable to forgive herself for it.",
    bio:"A brilliant, gentle researcher in Shinra's science division whose choices echo across the entire saga.",
    spoilerBio:"Sephiroth's biological mother. She agreed to bear a child injected with Jenova cells — a decision that destroyed her. She loved Vincent, and her sealed crystal cave becomes his eternal vigil.",
    tidbit:"Lucrecia's hidden Crystal Cave is one of the game's best-kept secrets, reachable only late with the submarine; visiting it unlocks Vincent's ultimate weapon, Death Penalty, and his final Limit Break, Chaos. She's seen weeping, sealed in crystal, unable to die.",
    portrait:{ skin:"#f0caa6", hair:"#4a3322", style:"long", eyes:"#6a4a3a", clothes:"#cfd2d4", acc:["glasses"] } },

  { id:"kadaj", name:"Kadaj", faction:"antagonist", role:"Remnant of Sephiroth",
    personality:"Volatile and childlike, swinging from petulant tantrums to chilling cruelty, Kadaj is a lost boy searching for a 'mother' he can barely name. His desperate, grief-stricken need to belong makes him as pitiable as he is dangerous.",
    bio:"A silver-haired youth leading his 'brothers' Loz and Yazoo in a search for 'Mother' two years after Meteorfall.",
    spoilerBio:"Kadaj and his brothers are physical Remnants of Sephiroth's will, born of the Lifestream's lingering Jenova cells. Kadaj absorbs Jenova's remains to become Sephiroth reborn — until Cloud cuts him down once more (Advent Children).",
    tidbit:"The three Remnants represent fragments of Sephiroth's personality: Kadaj his ego and will, Yazoo his charm and cruelty, Loz his raw strength and childishness. When Kadaj merges with Jenova's cells and 'becomes' Sephiroth, his final words — dissolving into the Lifestream as a frightened child — are quietly tragic.",
    portrait:{ skin:"#ead2c2", hair:"#c9ced2", style:"short", eyes:"#43d977", glow:true, slit:true, clothes:"#14161a" } },

  { id:"loz", name:"Loz", faction:"antagonist", role:"Remnant of Sephiroth",
    personality:"A hulking bruiser with a baby's heart — Loz is brutally strong yet astonishingly childish, throwing tantrums and even crying mid-fight. Utterly devoted to his brothers and their lost mother.",
    bio:"One of the three silver-haired Remnants in Advent Children, fighting with raw speed and a lightning-charged fist.",
    tidbit:"Despite being a terrifying physical powerhouse, Loz bursts into tears at the slightest provocation — a recurring gag that fans adore. His weapon, the Dual Hound, is an electric device that lets him move in near-teleporting bursts of speed.",
    portrait:{ skin:"#ead2c2", hair:"#c9ced2", style:"short", eyes:"#43d977", glow:true, slit:true, clothes:"#14161a" } },

  { id:"yazoo", name:"Yazoo", faction:"antagonist", role:"Remnant of Sephiroth",
    personality:"Cool, soft-spoken and eerily calm, Yazoo is the composed, manipulative counterpoint to Loz's tantrums. His languid charm masks a serene cruelty.",
    bio:"The elegant gunslinger among the three Remnants, unhurried even in violence.",
    tidbit:"Yazoo's calm, almost seductive menace and his weapon Velvet Nightmare (a gunblade) made him an instant fan favorite. He and Loz fuse into a single explosive attack against Cloud in their final moments rather than be left behind by Kadaj.",
    portrait:{ skin:"#ead2c2", hair:"#c9ced2", style:"long", eyes:"#43d977", glow:true, slit:true, clothes:"#14161a" } },

  { id:"weiss", name:"Weiss", keys:["Weiss"], faction:"antagonist", role:"Weiss the Immaculate · Commander of Deepground",
    personality:"Arrogant, bombastic and gloriously theatrical, Weiss revels in his own supremacy and slaughters with operatic glee. A peerless warrior whose pride blinds him to the strings being pulled behind his throne.",
    bio:"The ruthless, white-haired supreme commander of Deepground, Shinra's secret subterranean army.",
    spoilerBio:"Manipulated to become the vessel for Omega WEAPON — the Planet's final failsafe that would gather all Lifestream and abandon a dead world. Vincent stops him (Dirge of Cerberus).",
    tidbit:"Weiss fights bare-chested with twin gunblades and was the optional superboss of Dirge of Cerberus before becoming a story boss in the International release. The data of his brother Nero was secretly implanted in him — the seed of his transformation into Omega's host.",
    portrait:{ skin:"#f0d6c4", hair:"#f0f0f0", style:"long", eyes:"#43c8e6", glow:true, clothes:"#d8d8d8" } },

  { id:"nero", name:"Nero", keys:["Nero"], faction:"antagonist", role:"Nero the Sable · Tsviet",
    personality:"Quiet, devoted and unsettlingly serene, Nero commands darkness itself and lives only for his brother Weiss. His calm conceals a void-like power and a love so total it becomes catastrophic.",
    bio:"One of Deepground's elite Tsviets, able to engulf foes in absolute darkness.",
    spoilerBio:"Nero is Weiss's younger brother, born of darkness; their fatal bond is central to Deepground's downfall and the awakening of Omega.",
    tidbit:"Nero was born in darkness and his mother died in childbirth — Deepground later tried to dispose of him, but his power over a void-like 'darkness' made him too dangerous to kill. When he merges with Weiss near the end, he becomes the catalyst that awakens Omega WEAPON.",
    portrait:{ skin:"#d8c8c0", hair:"#14110f", style:"short", eyes:"#c45bff", glow:true, clothes:"#14110f" } },

  { id:"shelke", name:"Shelke Rui", short:"Shelke", keys:["Shelke"], faction:"ally", role:"Tsviet · Synaptic Net Diver",
    personality:"Outwardly flat, clinical and emotionless after a life as a living weapon, Shelke struggles to reconnect with the feelings stolen from her. Beneath the cold logic is a frightened girl slowly relearning how to be human.",
    bio:"A Deepground operative whose mind can dive into the world's information networks; she defects and aids Vincent.",
    spoilerBio:"Robbed of her childhood and frozen in a child's body by Mako, Shelke carries Lucrecia's preserved memories — the key that helps Vincent understand his past and stop Omega.",
    tidbit:"Shelke is chronologically an adult but trapped in a nine-year-old's body because heavy Mako infusion halted her aging. By absorbing Lucrecia's 'Synaptic Net Dive' data, she effectively carries another woman's memories — and is the one who explains Vincent's own past to him.",
    portrait:{ skin:"#f0caa6", hair:"#b8632e", style:"short", eyes:"#54b85f", glow:true, clothes:"#2a2f3a" } },

  { id:"rosso", name:"Rosso", keys:["Rosso"], faction:"antagonist", role:"Rosso the Crimson · Tsviet",
    personality:"Bloodthirsty, sensual and utterly without restraint, Rosso treats slaughter as ecstasy. Proud and unhinged, she would rather destroy herself than suffer defeat.",
    bio:"The crimson-clad berserker among Deepground's Tsviets, who revels in carnage.",
    tidbit:"True to her 'rather die than lose' nature, Rosso ends her fight with Vincent by hurling herself off a cliff rather than accept defeat. The Tsviets are color-coded — Weiss (white), Rosso (red), Azul (blue), Nero (black) — a deliberate palette of Deepground's elite.",
    portrait:{ skin:"#f0caa6", hair:"#c43a3a", style:"long", eyes:"#c45bff", glow:true, clothes:"#6a1414" } },

  { id:"azul", name:"Azul", keys:["Azul"], faction:"antagonist", role:"Azul the Cerulean · Tsviet",
    personality:"A mountainous warrior who lives for the thrill of overwhelming force, Azul is a proud, battle-hungry brute who measures all worth in raw strength.",
    bio:"The giant among the Tsviets, able to transform into a monstrous beast on the battlefield.",
    tidbit:"Azul can transform into a colossal four-legged beast called Arch Azul, and was experimented on so heavily that he barely registers as human. He guards a secret most don't suspect: ties to the original Turks and the deepest Deepground projects.",
    portrait:{ skin:"#6e4a35", hair:"#1a2a3a", style:"bald", eyes:"#43c8e6", glow:true, clothes:"#2a3a4a", acc:["beard"] } },

  { id:"marlene", name:"Marlene Wallace", short:"Marlene", faction:"ally", role:"Barret's daughter",
    personality:"Gentle, perceptive and wise beyond her years, Marlene is the quiet heart that keeps Barret human. Calm and caring even amid catastrophe, she often understands the adults' feelings better than they do.",
    bio:"The little girl Barret raises as his own and the emotional center he fights to protect, waiting out the war in Tifa's care.",
    spoilerBio:"Marlene is in truth the daughter of Barret's friend Dyne; Barret took her in after the destruction of Corel and has loved her as his own ever since.",
    tidbit:"In Advent Children, it's Marlene — not any of the adults — who most clearly voices the film's theme, scolding Cloud for running from his family. She's also the one who keeps the cast's letters and holds the group together while Cloud withdraws.",
    portrait:{ skin:"#ecc6a0", hair:"#4a3322", style:"braid", eyes:"#5a3a2e", clothes:"#c23a4a", acc:["bow"] } },

  { id:"dyne", name:"Dyne", keys:["Dyne"], faction:"ally", role:"Survivor of Corel · Marlene's father",
    personality:"Once a warm family man, Dyne is hollowed into a vengeful, broken shell by losing everything he loved. Consumed by grief, he can no longer tell justice from destruction — a mirror of the man Barret might have become.",
    bio:"Barret's closest friend from the coal town of Corel, who shared the same gun-arm fate and the same tragedy.",
    spoilerBio:"After Corel burned, Dyne survived but lost his wife and his mind, becoming a nihilistic killer. Reunited with Barret at the Gold Saucer, he takes his own life — entrusting his daughter Marlene to his friend.",
    tidbit:"Dyne and Barret fell from the same cliff during Corel's destruction — Barret survived with a maimed right arm, Dyne with a maimed right arm too. Both replaced it with a gun, making them literal dark mirrors. Dyne's quiet last act is asking after the daughter he can no longer face.",
    portrait:{ skin:"#6e4a35", hair:"#16140f", style:"buzz", eyes:"#241c14", clothes:"#3a3326", acc:["beard"] } },

  { id:"elmyra", name:"Elmyra Gainsborough", short:"Elmyra", faction:"ally", role:"Aerith's adoptive mother",
    personality:"Warm, steady and quietly courageous, Elmyra is an ordinary woman with extraordinary compassion. Fiercely protective of Aerith, she carries old griefs of her own with grace.",
    bio:"The kind widow of Sector 5 who took in a frightened child from the train station and raised her as her own.",
    spoilerBio:"Elmyra adopted Aerith after finding the dying Cetra Ifalna and her little girl at the Midgar station — keeping Aerith's heritage, and Shinra's interest, at bay for as long as she could.",
    tidbit:"Elmyra's own husband never returned from the war that Shinra waged — she went to the station day after day to wait for him, and it was there she instead met the dying Ifalna and adopted Aerith. She also quietly takes in Marlene during the events of the game.",
    portrait:{ skin:"#e8c8a0", hair:"#6e5a44", style:"neat", eyes:"#5a4636", clothes:"#6a5a3a" } },

  { id:"ifalna", name:"Ifalna", keys:["Ifalna"], faction:"cetra", role:"Cetra · Aerith's mother",
    personality:"Gentle and wise like the daughter she leaves behind, Ifalna bears the sorrow of being among the very last of her kind. Loving and brave, she gives everything to give Aerith a chance at life.",
    bio:"One of the final true Cetra, who could hear the Planet's voice.",
    spoilerBio:"Studied by Shinra as a specimen, Ifalna fell in love with the defecting Professor Gast and bore his child, Aerith. After Hojo killed Gast and held them captive for years, she escaped with Aerith, dying at the Midgar station.",
    tidbit:"The 'Gast Reports' — optional video reels found late in the game at Icicle Inn — are interviews Gast filmed with Ifalna, and the only way to hear the full, true history of the Cetra and Jenova in her own words. They're entirely missable.",
    portrait:{ skin:"#f0caa6", hair:"#5a4030", style:"long", eyes:"#54b85f", clothes:"#cfd2d4" } },

  { id:"gast", name:"Gast", keys:["Gast"], faction:"shinra", role:"Professor · Founder of the Jenova Project",
    personality:"A genuine, humane scientist driven by wonder rather than cruelty — the rare Shinra researcher with a conscience. When the truth horrifies him, he has the courage to abandon everything for love and for what is right.",
    bio:"Shinra's foremost authority on the Cetra and the original head of the Jenova Project — Hojo's mentor and rival.",
    spoilerBio:"Gast realized Jenova was not a Cetra but the Calamity, and abandoned Shinra in horror. He married the true Cetra Ifalna and fathered Aerith. Hojo tracked him down and murdered him to seize his family for study.",
    tidbit:"Gast Faremis was Shinra's greatest scientist and the one who actually misidentified Jenova as a Cetra — the original sin that begins everything. His reels reveal he later realized his catastrophic error, making the entire tragedy a chain reaction from one honest scientist's mistake and his ruthless successor.",
    portrait:{ skin:"#e3bd92", hair:"#cfc8b8", style:"neat", eyes:"#4a3a2e", clothes:"#cfd2d4", acc:["beard"] } },

  { id:"bugenhagen", name:"Bugenhagen", keys:["Bugenhagen"], faction:"ally", role:"Elder of Cosmo Canyon",
    personality:"A serene, twinkly-eyed sage who floats on his own contraption and chuckles 'Ho ho hooo'. Patient and profound, he speaks of the Planet and the Lifestream with the gentle authority of a man at peace with mortality.",
    bio:"The ancient scholar of Cosmo Canyon who teaches the party the truth of the Lifestream, and Red XIII's grandfather.",
    tidbit:"Bugenhagen's planetarium is where the game finally spells out its central ecology — that all life is the Lifestream, borrowed and returned. He's 130 years old, knows he's near the end, and his quiet passing in Advent Children's backstory is what spurs Nanaki to fully grow up.",
    portrait:{ skin:"#d8b48c", hair:"#eeeeee", style:"elder", eyes:"#4a3a2e", clothes:"#4a5a3a", acc:["beard"] } },

  { id:"zangan", name:"Zangan", keys:["Zangan"], faction:"ally", role:"Martial arts master",
    personality:"A genial, globe-trotting teacher with a humble, generous spirit, Zangan travels the world spreading his craft. Unassuming and kind, he quietly does the right thing without seeking thanks.",
    bio:"Tifa's martial arts master, whose training shapes her into the fighter she becomes.",
    spoilerBio:"On the night Nibelheim burned, Zangan pulled the mortally wounded Tifa from the flames and carried her to safety, saving her life.",
    tidbit:"Zangan never appears as more than a background figure, but a letter from him — easily missed — reveals he was the one who rescued the dying Tifa from Nibelheim and got her to the slums. He claims to have over 100 students worldwide.",
    portrait:{ skin:"#d8a878", hair:"#2a2622", style:"short", eyes:"#3a2e2e", clothes:"#6a4a2e", acc:["beard"] } },

  /* ---------- SIDE CHARACTERS ---------- */
  { id:"jessie", name:"Jessie", keys:["Jessie"], faction:"avalanche", role:"AVALANCHE · Demolitions & forgery",
    personality:"Spirited, flirtatious and warmhearted, Jessie is the bomb-maker who lightens the cell's grim work with jokes and an open crush on Cloud. Braver and more conflicted about the collateral damage than she lets on.",
    bio:"The AVALANCHE member who builds the bombs and forges the IDs for the reactor raids — and isn't shy about flirting with the new merc.",
    tidbit:"Jessie barely speaks in the 1997 original, but Remake reinvents her into a breakout fan-favorite with a full backstory: a former Gold Saucer stage actress whose father was left comatose by Mako exposure, which is why she fights Shinra.",
    portrait:{ skin:"#ecc6a0", hair:"#3a2a22", style:"short", eyes:"#5a3a2e", clothes:"#3a3a3a", acc:["headband"] } },

  { id:"biggs", name:"Biggs", keys:["Biggs"], faction:"avalanche", role:"AVALANCHE member",
    personality:"Steady, loyal and quietly competent, Biggs is the dependable hand of Barret's cell — the one who keeps his head when the others run hot.",
    bio:"One of Barret's AVALANCHE fighters in the Sector 7 cell, alongside Wedge and Jessie.",
    tidbit:"'Biggs and Wedge' are recurring names across nearly every Final Fantasy, lifted from the Rebel pilots in Star Wars. In Remake, Biggs is strongly implied to have survived the plate collapse — a small mercy the original never granted him.",
    portrait:{ skin:"#e3bd92", hair:"#2a2218", style:"short", eyes:"#3a2e2e", clothes:"#3a4a3a" } },

  { id:"wedge", name:"Wedge", keys:["Wedge"], faction:"avalanche", role:"AVALANCHE member",
    personality:"Gentle, food-loving and a little insecure, Wedge is the soft heart of the cell — eager to belong and braver than he believes himself to be.",
    bio:"The kind-hearted, heavyset member of Barret's Sector 7 AVALANCHE cell.",
    tidbit:"Wedge is the cell's animal-lover and worrier; Remake gives him a houseful of rescued cats. Like Biggs, his name is a Star Wars homage, and Remake teases that he too may have survived Sector 7 — before complicating it further.",
    portrait:{ skin:"#e8c39a", hair:"#2a2218", style:"short", eyes:"#3a2e2e", clothes:"#3a4a3a" } },

  { id:"scarlet", name:"Scarlet", keys:["Scarlet"], faction:"shinra", role:"Head of Weapons Development",
    personality:"Haughty, cruel and theatrically vicious, Scarlet runs Shinra's arms program with a sadist's relish and a braying laugh. She enjoys her power far too much.",
    bio:"Shinra's Director of Weapons Development, responsible for the Sister Ray cannon and Shinra's heaviest war machines.",
    tidbit:"Scarlet's infamous slap-fight with Tifa atop a gas chamber is one of the original game's most bizarre scenes. She built the Proud Clod and the Sister Ray — the very cannon later turned, ironically, against Shinra's own enemies and WEAPON.",
    portrait:{ skin:"#f0caa6", hair:"#ecdf9a", style:"long", eyes:"#6a5a3a", clothes:"#b2324a" } },

  { id:"heidegger", name:"Heidegger", keys:["Heidegger"], faction:"shinra", role:"Head of Public Safety (military)",
    personality:"Blustering, brutal and sycophantic, Heidegger barks orders and the signature laugh 'Gya-haa-haa!' while failing upward. Quick to blame subordinates, slow to take responsibility.",
    bio:"The head of Shinra's military and the Turks, commanding the company's army and its public-safety crackdowns.",
    tidbit:"Heidegger oversees both SOLDIER and the Turks, and it's his department that authorizes dropping the Sector 7 plate. His and Scarlet's constant bickering — and shared, braying laughs — make them the comic-villain double act of Shinra's board.",
    portrait:{ skin:"#d8a878", hair:"#2a2622", style:"bald", eyes:"#241c14", clothes:"#2a3a2e", acc:["beard"] } },

  { id:"hollander", name:"Hollander", keys:["Hollander"], faction:"shinra", role:"Scientist · Project G",
    personality:"Bitter, grasping and resentful, Hollander is a second-rate scientist eaten alive by his rivalry with Hojo. He'll betray anyone to prove himself the better man.",
    bio:"The Shinra scientist behind Project G, the experiment that created Genesis and Angeal — and the degradation that doomed them.",
    spoilerBio:"Hollander loses the race to create the perfect being to his rival Hojo, and spends Crisis Core manipulating Genesis with promises of a cure, deepening the catastrophe he helped cause.",
    tidbit:"Project G ('G' for Genesis, or for Gillian — Angeal's mother, the true source of the Jenova-derived cells) was Hollander's bid to outdo Hojo's Project S (Sephiroth). His failure and bitterness are the quiet engine behind the entire Crisis Core tragedy.",
    portrait:{ skin:"#d8b48c", hair:"#b0a890", style:"neat", eyes:"#4a3a2e", clothes:"#cfd2d4", acc:["beard"] } },

  /* ---------- EVER CRISIS · "THE FIRST SOLDIER" ---------- */
  { id:"glenn", name:"Glenn Lodbrok", keys:["Glenn"], faction:"soldier", role:"Prototype SOLDIER · Class P0",
    personality:"Upbeat and irrepressibly optimistic, Glenn cracks jokes even mid-battle. Brash and impulsive — he leaps before he looks — but blessed with reliable instincts and a fierce loyalty to his squad.",
    bio:"The lead of Ever Crisis's original arc 'The First Soldier': one of Shinra's earliest prototype 'P0' SOLDIERs, deployed to the remote Rhadore Archipelago to scout a Mako reactor site.",
    tidbit:"Tetsuya Nomura named Glenn after the 'green' in the matcha tea he was drinking while naming the crew. Stranger still, Glenn was designed for FFVII Rebirth FIRST, then retroactively given his Ever Crisis origin story — and he does cameo in Rebirth.",
    portrait:{ skin:"#e0b48a", hair:"#27221c", style:"messy", eyes:"#5fe3ff", glow:true, clothes:"#2a3a3a" } },

  { id:"lucia", name:"Lucia Lin", keys:["Lucia"], faction:"soldier", role:"Prototype SOLDIER · Sniper · P0",
    personality:"A fierce, ever-vigilant warrior whose razor perception makes her the squad's eyes — but also leaves her tense, anxious, and quick to expect the worst. A natural leader within the Shinra Army.",
    bio:"The sniper of Glenn's prototype SOLDIER trio in 'The First Soldier,' as sharp with a rifle as she is wary of everyone around her.",
    tidbit:"Lucia was among the very first wholly original characters created for Ever Crisis, debuting alongside Glenn and Matt — a rare case of new canon being built specifically for a mobile entry in the Compilation.",
    portrait:{ skin:"#ecc6a0", hair:"#1c1814", style:"long", eyes:"#5fe3ff", glow:true, clothes:"#2a2f36" } },

  { id:"matt", name:"Matt Winsord", keys:["Matt"], faction:"soldier", role:"Prototype SOLDIER · P0",
    personality:"Level-headed and quick-witted, Matt is the steady judgment of the trio — the one who reads a risky situation clearly and finds the smart way through where Glenn would just charge in.",
    bio:"The third prototype 'P0' SOLDIER of Glenn's unit, relied on for cool-headed calls on dangerous missions like the Rhadore expedition.",
    tidbit:"Matt rounds out Ever Crisis's original SOLDIER trio. Their Rhadore mission is the lens through which 'The First Soldier' shows the dawn of the SOLDIER program — and a young Sephiroth learning, briefly, how to fight as part of a team.",
    portrait:{ skin:"#d8a878", hair:"#2a2218", style:"short", eyes:"#5fe3ff", glow:true, clothes:"#2a3a3a" } },

  /* ---------- REMAKE / REBIRTH ORIGINALS ---------- */
  { id:"chadley", name:"Chadley", keys:["Chadley"], faction:"ally", role:"Research operative · Materia developer",
    personality:"Polite, precise and disarmingly formal, Chadley is endlessly eager to gather 'combat data' and turn it into new Materia. His earnest, slightly uncanny enthusiasm makes him equal parts helpful and meme-worthy.",
    bio:"A young researcher in Remake and Rebirth who equips Cloud's party with battle intel and, crucially, the Summon Materia earned by clearing his combat simulations. Assisted by an AI named Mai.",
    spoilerBio:"Rebirth reveals Chadley (and Mai) to be an artificial being built on the research of Professor Gast, secretly dedicated to studying the planet and undermining Shinra from within — a hidden heir to Gast's legacy.",
    tidbit:"Chadley's habit of interrupting exploration with 'Cloud, I've detected Mako readings nearby…' made him a fan-favorite meme. He's also the gatekeeper to nearly every summon in the remakes — you don't get Bahamut, Leviathan, or the others without beating his VR battles.",
    portrait:{ skin:"#8a6a4f", hair:"#161210", style:"short", eyes:"#5fd0ff", glow:true, clothes:"#3a4048", acc:["glasses"] } },

  { id:"roche", name:"Roche", keys:["Roche"], faction:"soldier", role:"SOLDIER 3rd Class",
    personality:"A theatrical adrenaline junkie obsessed with speed and the thrill of battle, Roche calls worthy foes 'my friend' and lives for the next duel. All flamboyant bravado at full throttle.",
    bio:"A motorcycle-riding SOLDIER 3rd Class introduced in Remake, who challenges Cloud to a high-speed bike duel through Midgar.",
    tidbit:"Nicknamed 'Speed Demon,' Roche is an entirely Remake-original character whose over-the-top bike boss fight became a standout set piece — and a small homage to FFVII's love of vehicle chases.",
    portrait:{ skin:"#e8c39a", hair:"#c9b079", style:"slick", eyes:"#5fe3ff", glow:true, clothes:"#2a3a3a", acc:["goggles"] } },

  { id:"sonon", name:"Sonon Kusakabe", short:"Sonon", keys:["Sonon"], faction:"ally", role:"Wutai operative",
    personality:"Disciplined, principled and protective, Sonon carries the quiet grief of Wutai's defeat. Steadfast and selfless, he fights with a staff and a older-brother's care for his reckless partner.",
    bio:"Yuffie's partner in the Remake INTERmission episode, a Wutai operative sent with her to infiltrate Shinra and steal its 'ultimate Materia.'",
    tidbit:"Sonon trained under Yuffie's late mentor and lost his sister in the Sector 7 plate collapse, giving Wutai's war with Shinra a personal face. His synergized combat with Yuffie introduced the team-attack system later expanded in Rebirth.",
    portrait:{ skin:"#e0b48a", hair:"#1c1814", style:"neat", eyes:"#2a2018", clothes:"#2f4f54", acc:["ponytail"] } },

  /* ---------- ORIGINAL GAME & ADVENT CHILDREN ---------- */
  { id:"caitsith", name:"Cait Sith", keys:["Cait Sith"], faction:"ally", role:"Fortune-telling robot · Reeve's puppet",
    personality:"A cheeky, theatrical showman who tells fortunes through a megaphone and rides a giant Moogle. All comic bravado on the surface — but when it counts he proves unexpectedly, movingly brave.",
    bio:"The toy-like robot cat that joins Cloud's party, remote-controlled by the Shinra executive Reeve. It fights with a megaphone, slots, and dice.",
    spoilerBio:"Cait Sith is Reeve's puppet — first planted as a Shinra spy. When cornered, the first unit sacrifices itself to save the group, and Reeve simply sends in a replacement, making Cait Sith the one party member who can 'die' and come back.",
    tidbit:"Cait Sith's slot-machine Limit Break includes 'Game Over,' a 1-in-64 jackpot that instantly kills every enemy on screen — or, on bad luck, the whole party. He's also the only party member who is never physically present.",
    portrait:{ style:"cat", clothes:"#7a1f2a" } },

  { id:"corneo", name:"Don Corneo", short:"Corneo", keys:["Corneo"], faction:"ally", role:"Don of Wall Market",
    personality:"A lecherous, gaudy, cackling crime boss whose courage evaporates the instant he's cornered. Greedy and grotesque, he treats people as playthings — until someone scarier walks in.",
    bio:"The sleazy kingpin of Midgar's Wall Market, who 'auditions' brides and unwittingly drags Cloud — in disguise — into his mansion.",
    tidbit:"Corneo is the reason for FFVII's infamous cross-dressing sequence: to reach him, Cloud must dress as a woman, a scene Remake reinvented into a triumphant Honeybee Inn dance number with Andrea Rhodea.",
    portrait:{ skin:"#d8b48c", hair:"#1a1a1a", style:"bald", eyes:"#2a2018", clothes:"#6a2a6a", acc:["beard"] } },

  { id:"palmer", name:"Palmer", keys:["Palmer"], faction:"shinra", role:"Head of the Space Program",
    personality:"A gluttonous, cowardly buffoon of an executive, forever sipping tea and dodging blame. Comic-relief Shinra brass with none of the menace and all of the greed.",
    bio:"The rotund head of Shinra's defunct Space Program, whose neglect helped ground Cid Highwind's dream of spaceflight.",
    tidbit:"Palmer's the butt of one of the game's slapstick beats — he gets comically run over by the Tiny Bronco — and his tea order ('lard… and a little tea') is a long-running fan in-joke.",
    portrait:{ skin:"#e0b48a", hair:"#b0a890", style:"bald", eyes:"#3a2e2e", clothes:"#3a3326", acc:["mustache"] } },

  { id:"seto", name:"Seto", keys:["Seto"], faction:"ally", role:"Warrior of Cosmo Canyon · Red XIII's father",
    personality:"Silent and resolute, remembered wrongly as a coward but in truth the bravest of his tribe — a guardian who gave everything, and asked for nothing, to protect his home.",
    bio:"Red XIII's father, a warrior of Cosmo Canyon who defended the canyon from the invading Gi tribe.",
    spoilerBio:"Seto fought the Gi alone until their poison arrows turned him to stone — and he still stands sentinel over Cosmo Canyon to this day. Nanaki, who believed his father a deserter, learns the truth and finally honors him.",
    tidbit:"The reveal of Seto, petrified mid-roar above Cosmo Canyon as Bugenhagen tells his story, is one of FFVII's quiet emotional high points — and the moment Red XIII grows up.",
    portrait:{ skin:"#9a9488", hair:"#6e6a60", style:"beast", eyes:"#9ad6ff", clothes:"#5a564c", acc:["scar"] } },

  { id:"denzel", name:"Denzel", keys:["Denzel"], faction:"ally", role:"Orphan of Edge",
    personality:"A quiet, watchful boy hardened by loss yet aching to belong. Brave beyond his years, he looks to Cloud as the hero — and the family — he needs.",
    bio:"An orphan from the Sector 7 slums who lost his parents in Meteorfall and is taken in by Cloud and Tifa, living with them and Marlene at Seventh Heaven.",
    spoilerBio:"Denzel is stricken with Geostigma in Advent Children, and his quiet suffering is part of what finally pulls Cloud out of his guilt. He's cured by the healing rain at the film's end.",
    tidbit:"Denzel headlines his own anime short, 'Final Fantasy VII: Last Order' / 'On the Way to a Smile — Case of Denzel,' which fills in how he survived the plate fall and found his way to Cloud and Tifa.",
    portrait:{ skin:"#ecc6a0", hair:"#7a5a3a", style:"short", eyes:"#5a4030", clothes:"#4a5a4a" } },

  /* ---------- CRISIS CORE ---------- */
  { id:"lazard", name:"Lazard", keys:["Lazard"], faction:"shinra", role:"Director of SOLDIER",
    personality:"Polished, ambitious and quietly bitter, Lazard plays the loyal company man while nursing a grudge against the father who disowned him. Beneath the bureaucrat is a man searching for a cause worth his loyalty.",
    bio:"The bespectacled Director of SOLDIER in Crisis Core, who oversees Zack and the response to Genesis's defection.",
    spoilerBio:"Lazard is revealed to be an illegitimate son of President Shinra, cast aside from the succession. He betrays the company to aid Genesis, ultimately succumbing to degradation as a Genesis copy — dying at peace having chosen his own side.",
    tidbit:"Lazard's full name, Lazard Deusericus, and his quiet kinship with Rufus (both Shinra sons, raised worlds apart) make him one of Crisis Core's most subtly tragic figures.",
    portrait:{ skin:"#ecc6a0", hair:"#ecdf9a", style:"neat", eyes:"#6a86a8", clothes:"#cfd2d4", acc:["glasses"] } },

  { id:"kunsel", name:"Kunsel", keys:["Kunsel"], faction:"soldier", role:"SOLDIER 2nd Class",
    personality:"Easygoing, sharp and improbably well-informed, Kunsel is the friend who always seems to know what's really going on. Loyal and grounded, he's the normal life Zack keeps almost reaching.",
    bio:"Zack's dependable SOLDIER friend in Crisis Core, who keeps him fed with intel, gossip, and a steady stream of emails.",
    tidbit:"Kunsel is never once seen without his helmet, and his encyclopedic knowledge of Shinra's secrets has spawned a popular fan theory that he quietly knew the whole conspiracy all along.",
    portrait:{ skin:"#e3bd92", hair:"#3a2e22", style:"short", eyes:"#5fe3ff", glow:true, clothes:"#2a2f36" } },

  { id:"gillian", name:"Gillian Hewley", short:"Gillian", keys:["Gillian"], faction:"shinra", role:"Scientist · Angeal's mother",
    personality:"Gentle, dutiful and crushed by guilt, Gillian carries the weight of a science she helped birth. A loving mother who comes to believe her own death is the only amends she can make.",
    bio:"Angeal's mother and a former Shinra researcher — herself the original subject of Project G.",
    spoilerBio:"Gillian's cells (derived from Jenova) are the true source of the 'G' in Project G, passed to Angeal and Genesis. Unable to bear what the project did to her son, she takes her own life.",
    tidbit:"Because the 'G-cells' trace back to Gillian rather than to Genesis, she — not Hollander or Hojo — is arguably the genetic mother of the entire SOLDIER degradation crisis.",
    portrait:{ skin:"#e8c8a0", hair:"#6e5a44", style:"neat", eyes:"#5a4636", clothes:"#cfd2d4" } },

  /* ---------- BEFORE CRISIS (original Turks & AVALANCHE) ---------- */
  { id:"veld", name:"Veld", keys:["Veld"], faction:"turks", role:"Leader of the Turks (original)",
    personality:"Stern, weathered and intensely loyal — to Shinra, and to a secret that pulls the other way. A commander who has buried his conscience deep, and finds it again too late.",
    bio:"The original commander of the Turks in Before Crisis, and Tseng's predecessor, leading the hunt against AVALANCHE.",
    spoilerBio:"Veld is secretly the father of Elfé, the leader of the very AVALANCHE he's hunting — having believed his family killed in a Shinra operation years before. In the end he turns on Shinra to save her.",
    tidbit:"Veld (localized from 'Verdot') anchors Before Crisis's whole tragedy: a Turk leader whose loyalty to Shinra and love for his lost daughter are on a collision course from the first episode.",
    portrait:{ skin:"#d8b48c", hair:"#3a342e", style:"neat", eyes:"#3a2e2e", clothes:"#14161a", acc:["beard"] } },

  { id:"elfe", name:"Elfé", short:"Elfé", keys:["Elfé","Elfe"], faction:"avalanche", role:"Leader of (original) AVALANCHE",
    personality:"Cold, commanding and quietly dying, Elfé leads with iron resolve while a borrowed power eats her alive. Beneath the icy general is a daughter robbed of her name and her past.",
    bio:"The enigmatic leader of the original AVALANCHE in Before Crisis, who wields a Materia of terrible power.",
    spoilerBio:"Elfé's true name is Felicia — she is Veld's lost daughter, kept alive and controlled by the Zirconiade Materia fused into her body, and manipulated by the zealot Fuhito.",
    tidbit:"Elfé predates Barret's AVALANCHE by years; Before Crisis reframes 'AVALANCHE' not as one cell but as a movement, with Elfé's tragic, doomed faction as its first and most extreme incarnation.",
    portrait:{ skin:"#ecc6a0", hair:"#c4bcd6", style:"long", eyes:"#6a5a8a", clothes:"#2a2f3a" } },

  { id:"fuhito", name:"Fuhito", keys:["Fuhito"], faction:"avalanche", role:"AVALANCHE's zealot",
    personality:"A cold, brilliant fanatic who despises humanity itself. To Fuhito the Planet can only be saved by erasing the people poisoning it — and he will sacrifice anyone, Elfé included, to do it.",
    bio:"The fanatical strategist of the original AVALANCHE, obsessed with summoning the destructive Materia Zirconiade to wipe out humankind.",
    tidbit:"Fuhito is the dark mirror of every later eco-warrior: he takes 'save the Planet' to its genocidal extreme, making Barret's AVALANCHE look restrained by comparison.",
    portrait:{ skin:"#d8c2a8", hair:"#1c1814", style:"slick", eyes:"#3a3a3a", clothes:"#2a2622", acc:["glasses"] } },

  { id:"shears", name:"Shears", keys:["Shears"], faction:"avalanche", role:"AVALANCHE warrior",
    personality:"A powerful, principled fighter devoted to Elfé and increasingly sickened by Fuhito's fanaticism. Loyal to people, not to dogma — and willing to break with the cause when it loses its soul.",
    bio:"Elfé's right hand and the muscle of the original AVALANCHE, who fights the Turks with mechanical gauntlets.",
    tidbit:"Shears's growing disgust with Fuhito's methods makes him one of Before Crisis's most sympathetic 'enemies,' and his arc quietly questions where the line between resistance and atrocity lies.",
    portrait:{ skin:"#d8a878", hair:"#1c1814", style:"short", eyes:"#3a2e2e", clothes:"#3a3a3a" } },

  /* ---------- DIRGE OF CERBERUS & WUTAI ---------- */
  { id:"shalua", name:"Shalua Rui", short:"Shalua", keys:["Shalua"], faction:"ally", role:"WRO scientist · Shelke's sister",
    personality:"Driven to the edge of self-destruction by a single purpose — finding her lost sister. Brilliant and reckless, she pours her broken body into the search, sparing nothing, least of all herself.",
    bio:"A scientist of Reeve's World Regenesis Organization in Dirge of Cerberus, who has spent years hunting for her sister, lost to Deepground.",
    spoilerBio:"Shalua lost an arm and an eye (replaced with cybernetics) in her search for Shelke. Reunited with her at last, she gives her life in Deepground — moments before fully understanding the child her sister had become.",
    tidbit:"Shalua and Shelke's relationship is the emotional core of Dirge of Cerberus: a sister who never stopped searching, and a sister frozen as a child who can barely remember being loved.",
    portrait:{ skin:"#e8c8a0", hair:"#3a2e22", style:"short", eyes:"#5fd0ff", glow:true, clothes:"#cfd2d4", acc:["scar"] } },

  { id:"godo", name:"Godo Kisaragi", short:"Godo", keys:["Godo"], faction:"ally", role:"Lord of Wutai · Yuffie's father",
    personality:"Proud but resigned, Godo carries the shame of Wutai's surrender like a stone. Stern and traditional, he clashes with his fiery daughter — though both, in truth, want the same lost glory back.",
    bio:"The ruler of Wutai and Yuffie's father, who laid down arms when Shinra defeated his nation in the Wutai War.",
    tidbit:"Godo's acceptance of Wutai's defeat is exactly what Yuffie rebels against — her Materia-stealing crusade is, at heart, a daughter trying to restore the pride her father gave up.",
    portrait:{ skin:"#d8a878", hair:"#2a2622", style:"neat", eyes:"#3a2e2e", clothes:"#5a2a2a", acc:["beard","ponytail"] } },
];

